titles.title: A concurrent resolution directing the Clerk of the House of Representatives to make a correction in the enrollment of H.R. 5895.
A concurrent resolution directing the Clerk of the House of Representatives to make a correction in the enrollment of H.R. 5895.

vote.text: Submitted in the Senate, considered, and agreed to without amendment by Unanimous Consent.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.
Mr. Frelinghuysen asked unanimous consent to take from the Speaker's table and consider.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: Directs the Clerk of the House of Representatives to make a correction in the enrollment of H.R. 5895 (Energy and Water, Legislative Branch, and Military Construction and Veterans Affairs Appropriations Act, 2019) to amend the title.
